\/","url_meta":{"origin":19388,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Riddah: The Prophet pardons an apostate traitor","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 15, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Abdullah ibn Sa\u2019d ibn Abi Sarh would write for the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but the devil deceived him and he joined the unbelievers. The Prophet ordered that he should be killed on the day of liberation, but Uthman ibn Affan sought\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/12\/prophet-always-recommends-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":19388,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Pardon: The Prophet always recommended forgiveness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: I never saw a case involving legal retaliation being referred to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but that he would command pardoning the criminal. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4497 Source:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21332,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/12\/16\/umar-hudud-punish-doubts\/","url_meta":{"origin":19388,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Hudud: Better to pardon than punish with doubts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 16, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibrahim al-Nakha\u2019i reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThat I relax the legal punishments is more beloved to me than applying them with doubts.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Ibn Abi\u0304 Shaybah 27926 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Sakhawi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0625\u0628\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0650\u064a\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064f \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11670,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/23\/pardon-better-than-punishing\/","url_meta":{"origin":19388,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hudud: Better to mistake in forgiveness than punishment","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 23, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAvoid applying legal punishments\u00a0against the Muslims if you are able. If the criminal has a way out, then leave him to his way. Verily, for the leader to err in pardoning is better than to err in\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u064